I tried to look into the problematic function (AllocateDataSpace:108) in `cuda_device_api.cc`. It seems that `cudaSetDevice()` does not able to find the device, and program builder just aborted from there. 

```c++
    if (ctx.device_type == kDLCPUPinned) {
      CUDA_CALL(cudaMallocHost(&ret, nbytes));
    } else {
      CUDA_CALL(cudaSetDevice(ctx.device_id));
      CUDA_CALL(cudaMalloc(&ret, nbytes));
    }
```

This is quite wired. Everything can run smoothly using the python API. But when using C++ APIs, the runtime cannot detect the device or context, and thus cannot find usable schedules.
